","before 1378":"vóór 1378","abt. 1400":"circa 1400","1450":"1450","1350":"1350","1460":"1460","1382":"1382","1490":"1490","1378":"1378","1400":"1400","1356":"1356","1398":"1398","1375":"1375","1406 ":"1406","1406":"1406","1416":"1416","England":"England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England":"Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England","Mildenhall, Suffolk, England":"Mildenhall, Suffolk, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Colmworth, Bedfordshire, England.":"Colmworth, Bedfordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1378–1450":"1378–1450","1375–1460":"1375–1460","1400–1490":"1400–1490","1406–1490":"1406–1490","1350–1416":"1350–1416","1356–1400":"1356–1400","before 1378":"before 1378","abt. 1400":"about 1400","1450":"1450","1350":"1350","1460":"1460","1382":"1382","1490":"1490","1378":"1378","1400":"1400","1356":"1356","1398":"1398","1375":"1375","1406 ":"1406","1406":"1406","1416":"1416","England":"England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England":"Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England","Mildenhall, Suffolk, England":"Mildenhall, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Colmworth, Bedfordshire, England.":"Colmworth, Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Spencer","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Yorkshire): occupational name for someone who dispensed provisions or money, from Middle English <i>spenser(e)</i>, <i>spencer(e)</i> ‘household steward, butler, almoner’ (Anglo-Norman French <i>espenser</i>, Old French <i>despensier</i>). Compare   Spence   and   Spender  . There is some dispute about the origins of the Spencer family, whose most famous member in recent times was the late Princess of Wales, born Lady Diana Spencer (1961–97). Some sources say that they are descended from William the Conqueror's steward, Robert Despencer. What is clear is that by the 15th century they had become prosperous from sheep farming in Northamptonshire. Robert Spencer (died 1627) was said to be the wealthiest man in England. Their titles have included Earls of Sunderland and Earls Spencer; and through the female line the 5th Earl of Sunderland also became Duke of Marlborough in 1733. This connection was the result of the marriage, in 1700, of the 3rd Duke of Sunderland to the daughter of John Churchill, 1st Duke of Marlborough. The youngest son of this union, John Spencer (1708–46), was the father of the 1st Earl Spencer (1734–83)."],"variants":[{"name":"Spence","meanings":["English and Scottish: nickname for a servant employed in the pantry of a great house or monastery, from Middle English <i>spense</i>, <i>spence</i> ‘pantry, larder, storeroom’ (Old French <i>despense</i>, from a Late Latin derivative of <i>dispendere</i>, past participle <i>dispensus</i> ‘to weigh out or dispense’). Compare   Spencer  ."]},{"name":"Spenser","meanings":["English: variant of   Spencer  ."]},{"name":"Spender","meanings":["English:","occupational name or status name from Middle English <i>spender(e)</i>, <i>spendour</i> ‘steward, treasurer’, a shortened form of Middle English, Old French <i>despendour</i>, denoting someone who managed money or supplies. Compare   Spencer  .","alternatively, perhaps a nickname from Middle English <i>spender(e)</i>, <i>spendour</i> ‘spender (of money), spendthrift’."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Maria</i> via Old Welsh <i>Meir</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":4,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Mary Spencer was born in 1378, in Mildenhall, Suffolk, England, her father, John Spencer, was 28 and her mother, Alice Deverill, was 23. She married John Pope II in 1398, in Mildenhall, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1450, in Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England, at the age of 72."},"et":{"1378–1450":"1378–1450","1375–1460":"1375–1460","1400–1490":"1400–1490","1406–1490":"1406–1490","1350–1416":"1350–1416","1356–1400":"1356–1400","before 1378":"enne 1378","abt. 1400":"umbes 1400","1450":"1450","1350":"1350","1460":"1460","1382":"1382","1490":"1490","1378":"1378","1400":"1400","1356":"1356","1398":"1398","1375":"1375","1406 ":"1406","1406":"1406","1416":"1416","England":"England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England":"Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England","Mildenhall, Suffolk, England":"Mildenhall, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Colmworth, Bedfordshire, England.":"Colmworth, Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1378–1450":"1378–1450","1375–1460":"1375–1460","1400–1490":"1400–1490","1406–1490":"1406–1490","1350–1416":"1350–1416","1356–1400":"1356–1400","before 1378":"ennen vuotta 1378","abt. 1400":"noin 1400","1450":"1450","1350":"1350","1460":"1460","1382":"1382","1490":"1490","1378":"1378","1400":"1400","1356":"1356","1398":"1398","1375":"1375","1406 ":"1406","1406":"1406","1416":"1416","England":"England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England":"Twyford, Buckinghamshire, England","Mildenhall, Suffolk, England":"Mildenhall, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Colmworth, Bedfordshire, England.":"Colmworth, Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1378–1450":"1378–1450","1375–1460":"1375–1460","1400–1490":"1400–1490","1406–1490":"1406–1490","1350–1416":"1350–1416","1356–1400":"1356–14